name: Nebuchadnezzar the great: King of Sumer and Akkad
description: He was the second king of the Neo-Babylonian Empire. he is typically regarded as the empire's greatest king. Ruling for 43 years, Nebuchadnezzar was the longest-reigning king of the Chaldean dynasty. At the time of his death, Nebuchadnezzar was among the most powerful rulers in the world.
